[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:55:27 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: emis.carer.0@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <904014856.1271.1673398527332@0b0946f6b810> Subject: Ms AZ Patient 1 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1268_1519378782.1673398527328" ------=_Part_1268_1519378782.1673398527328 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1269_972711007.1673398527328" ------=_Part_1269_972711007.1673398527328 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1270_1526921218.1673398527328" ------=_Part_1270_1526921218.1673398527328 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr Emis Carer-0, Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Ms AZ Patient 1 Please be my carer ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=r1iC8LeCez Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=r1iC8LeCez 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1270_1526921218.1673398527328 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr Emis Carer-0,

Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=r1iC8LeCez

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2144&temp=r1iC8LeCez
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team


w: http://www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us

[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:55:40 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: emis.carer.1@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <682552930.1287.1673398540127@0b0946f6b810> Subject: Ms AZ Patient 1 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1284_1237819883.1673398540124" ------=_Part_1284_1237819883.1673398540124 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1285_1988285445.1673398540124" ------=_Part_1285_1988285445.1673398540124 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1286_2002752570.1673398540124" ------=_Part_1286_2002752570.1673398540124 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr Emis Carer-1, Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Ms AZ Patient 1 Please be my carer ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2153&temp=Zu8GmxGob0 Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2153&temp=Zu8GmxGob0 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1286_2002752570.1673398540124 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr Emis Carer-1,

Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2153&temp=Zu8GmxGob0

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2153&temp=Zu8GmxGob0
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team


w: http://www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us

Dear Mr Emis Carer-2,

Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2161&temp=VFtD844Zmj

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2161&temp=VFtD844Zmj
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:56:07 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: emis.carer.3@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <817726056.1319.1673398567522@0b0946f6b810> Subject: Ms AZ Patient 1 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1316_165131101.1673398567517" ------=_Part_1316_165131101.1673398567517 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1317_555912264.1673398567517" ------=_Part_1317_555912264.1673398567517 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1318_1331969089.1673398567518" ------=_Part_1318_1331969089.1673398567518 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr Emis Carer-3, Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Ms AZ Patient 1 Please be my carer ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2169&temp=eXY1MpAFbb Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2169&temp=eXY1MpAFbb 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1318_1331969089.1673398567518 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr Emis Carer-3,

Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2169&temp=eXY1MpAFbb

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2169&temp=eXY1MpAFbb
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:56:20 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: emis.carer.4@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <516642566.1335.1673398580787@0b0946f6b810> Subject: Ms AZ Patient 1 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1332_606435359.1673398580783" ------=_Part_1332_606435359.1673398580783 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1333_1155339594.1673398580783" ------=_Part_1333_1155339594.1673398580783 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1334_64492613.1673398580783" ------=_Part_1334_64492613.1673398580783 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr Emis Carer-4, Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Ms AZ Patient 1 Please be my carer ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2177&temp=58KzTfnFy8 Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2177&temp=58KzTfnFy8 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1334_64492613.1673398580783 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr Emis Carer-4,

Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2177&temp=58KzTfnFy8

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2177&temp=58KzTfnFy8
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:56:34 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: emis.carer.5@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <521169050.1351.1673398594617@0b0946f6b810> Subject: Ms AZ Patient 1 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1348_1821115151.1673398594610" ------=_Part_1348_1821115151.1673398594610 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1349_984718206.1673398594610" ------=_Part_1349_984718206.1673398594610 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1350_2000913646.1673398594611" ------=_Part_1350_2000913646.1673398594611 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr Emis Carer-5, Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Ms AZ Patient 1 Please be my carer ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2185&temp=qrEUf89F9K Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2185&temp=qrEUf89F9K 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1350_2000913646.1673398594611 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr Emis Carer-5,

Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2185&temp=qrEUf89F9K

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2185&temp=qrEUf89F9K
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team


w: http://www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us

[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:56:47 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: emis.carer.6@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <1043835351.1367.1673398607972@0b0946f6b810> Subject: Ms AZ Patient 1 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1364_1254868853.1673398607966" ------=_Part_1364_1254868853.1673398607966 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1365_442620344.1673398607966" ------=_Part_1365_442620344.1673398607966 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1366_141345527.1673398607966" ------=_Part_1366_141345527.1673398607966 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr Emis Carer-6, Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Ms AZ Patient 1 Please be my carer ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2193&temp=RdEzL1l74z Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2193&temp=RdEzL1l74z 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1366_141345527.1673398607966 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr Emis Carer-6,

Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2193&temp=RdEzL1l74z

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2193&temp=RdEzL1l74z
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team


w: http://www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

Questions?

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team

[Date: Wed, 11 Jan 2023 00:57:14 +0000 (UTC) From: Patients Know Best To: emis.carer.8@pkbtest.com Message-ID: <511860138.1399.1673398634334@0b0946f6b810> Subject: Ms AZ Patient 1 would like to share their health record with you MIME-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----=_Part_1396_157989856.1673398634331" ------=_Part_1396_157989856.1673398634331 Content-Type: multipart/related; boundary="----=_Part_1397_1055771644.1673398634331" ------=_Part_1397_1055771644.1673398634331 Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary="----=_Part_1398_1529285924.1673398634331" ------=_Part_1398_1529285924.1673398634331 Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit Dear Mr Emis Carer-0, Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health. ---------- Message from Ms AZ Patient 1 Please be my carer ---------- To accept this invitation click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2209&temp=q9fnCISyMl Questions? 1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer. 2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2209&temp=q9fnCISyMl 3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely. You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Yours, Patients Know Best Help Team w: www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us e: help@pkbtest.com ------=_Part_1398_1529285924.1673398634331 Content-Type: text/html;charset=UTF-8 Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit

Dear Mr Emis Carer-0,

Ms AZ Patient 1 has invited you to access their medical information so you can help manage their health.

Message from Ms AZ Patient 1

Please be my carer

To accept this invitation click this link:

http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2209&temp=q9fnCISyMl

Questions?
  1. Is this secure? Patients Know Best is GDPR-compliant for European patients and HIPAA-compliant for US ones. The UK site is part of the NHS secure network (N3), so it already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click this link: http://pkb-frontend-3/registerPatientStart.action?uid=2209&temp=q9fnCISyMl
  3. What happens after I register? You can access the records of Ms AZ Patient 1 to use Patients Know Best together securely.

You are receiving this notification because you have been invited as a carer. Once registered, log in and review the people you care for by following this link: "http://pkb-frontend-3/patient/myDependents.action?tab=invitations&subTab=dependents"

Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team


w: http://www.patientsknowbest.com/contact-us
